This directory contains test cases for the following feature:
FEATURE: F2008: Recursive allocatable types

Overview:
Fortran 2008 standard allows derived types to contain allocatable
components of the the type being defined.  It also allows users
to elide allocatable components in structure constructors.

RTC work item:  28056 (recursive allocatable types)
RTC work item:  146334 (elide allocatable components in structure constructors)
github issue:  https://github.ibm.com/compiler/wyvern/issues/4332

The unit_tests/func subdirectory contains functional test cases
The unit_tests/diag subdirectory contains diagnostic test cases
